        "content": "<p>Do we have the standard basis for the space of matrices over a (nontrivial?) ring? Equivalently, the basis of <code>M →ₗ[R] N</code> induced by finite bases of <code>M</code> and <code>N</code>? Thank's!</p>",
        "id": 252311257,
        "sender_full_name": "Riccardo Brasca",
        "timestamp": 1631023882
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Since <code>matrix m n R</code> is just <code>m → n → R</code>, you might be able to get there by combining <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib_docs/find/pi.basis\">docs#pi.basis</a> with <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib_docs/find/pi.basis_fun\">docs#pi.basis_fun</a></p>",
